WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.918 --> 00:00:03.045
<i>Previously on </i>The Testaments...

2
00:00:03.128 --> 00:00:04.880
You're listening to Radio Free Boston

3
00:00:04.963 --> 00:00:07.090
with an urgent warning for...

4
00:00:07.174 --> 00:00:09.092
- Is something happening?
- Gilead's retaliating

5
00:00:09.176 --> 00:00:10.469
for what happened with the bus.

6
00:00:10.552 --> 00:00:13.055
- What's going on?
- The Aunts decide our contenders today.

7
00:00:13.138 --> 00:00:14.556
Two to three suitors each. usually.

8
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:16.183
Then house visits.
Then weddings.

9
00:00:16.266 --> 00:00:18.810
Jehosheba wants power.
Hulda. security.

10
00:00:18.894 --> 00:00:21.313
Agnes. I'm not sure what she wants.

11
00:00:21.396 --> 00:00:22.856
Not yet.

12
00:00:22.940 --> 00:00:24.233
Let's begin. shall we?

13
00:00:24.316 --> 00:00:25.776
Who wants to get married. anyway?

14
00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:27.361
After what happened at the Ball.

15
00:00:27.444 --> 00:00:29.947
you should be throwing yourself
at the mercy of Aunt Lydia.

16
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:32.241
Well maybe I'll get lucky.
and I won't get any offers.

17
00:00:32.324 --> 00:00:34.952
What is wrong with you?
This is our whole lives!

18
00:00:35.035 --> 00:00:37.329
Some people would give
anything for the right match.

19
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:39.289
May I have this dance?

20
00:00:40.082 --> 00:00:41.375
In His grace.

21
00:00:41.458 --> 00:00:43.168
If Commander MacKenzie
is meeting with the Japanese.

22
00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:45.170
we think he might be brokering
a deal for artillery...

23
00:00:45.254 --> 00:00:47.339
- How the fuck am I supposed to...
- Lower your voice.

24
00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:49.758
I don't think Agnes
will know anything about that.

25
00:00:49.841 --> 00:00:52.094
- I'm in love.
- Who?

26
00:00:52.177 --> 00:00:53.387
Garth.

27
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:54.930
He's soon to be made a Commander.

28
00:00:55.013 --> 00:00:57.933
I thought perhaps you might
make him eligible.

29
00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:00.727
I shall think the matter over.

30
00:01:00.811 --> 00:01:02.980
Only a few open slots left.

31
00:01:03.063 --> 00:01:06.358
I have another one to add to the mix.
Garth Chapin.

32
00:01:06.441 --> 00:01:10.112
- He's not eligible.
- He will be. Soon enough.

33
00:01:10.195 --> 00:01:12.823
Time to tell the girls' families.

34
00:01:13.532 --> 00:01:15.617
- Let me help you.
- Why?

35
00:01:15.701 --> 00:01:17.536
Because I know how you're feeling.

36
00:01:17.619 --> 00:01:19.580
Stay here.
Someone's gonna come get you.

37
00:01:19.663 --> 00:01:20.747
You're leaving me alone?

38
00:01:22.332 --> 00:01:25.085
You are never alone.

39
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:30.048
This is Radio Free Boston with an update.

40
00:01:30.132 --> 00:01:33.427
Gilead Forces' recent
attempt to invade Boston

41
00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:37.806
was unsuccessful.
and loss of life for Gilead was high.

42
00:01:37.889 --> 00:01:40.976
The violence at the border
has prompted dignitaries from Canada

43
00:01:41.059 --> 00:01:43.562
and the American government
to convene with the UN...

44
00:01:43.645 --> 00:01:46.064
Of course. that's not
what people here were told.

45
00:01:46.148 --> 00:01:48.734
Even if someone in Gilead knew the truth.

46
00:01:48.817 --> 00:01:50.444
who was gonna tell?

47
00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:52.487
Not me. That's for sure.

48
00:01:52.571 --> 00:01:54.865
If I was discovered as Mayday.

49
00:01:54.948 --> 00:01:57.075
I would be tortured and killed.

50
00:02:23.393 --> 00:02:24.561
More coffee?

51
00:02:24.645 --> 00:02:27.314
Uh. no. Thanks.

52
00:02:31.902 --> 00:02:33.528
June had told me to wait.

53
00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:36.657
That someone would come get me.

54
00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:37.866
I waited.

55
00:02:39.076 --> 00:02:40.494
But no one came.

56
00:02:56.134 --> 00:02:58.470
Sorry to kick you out.

57
00:02:59.513 --> 00:03:00.806
Where do you have to be?

58
00:03:00.889 --> 00:03:02.974
Here. I need to be here.

59
00:03:03.058 --> 00:03:06.687
Well. on the bright side.

60
00:03:06.770 --> 00:03:08.814
tomorrow's supposed to be
a beautiful May day.

61
00:03:08.897 --> 00:03:10.607
It's fucking March!

62
00:03:14.653 --> 00:03:17.322
Ah. I didn't think you'd last.

63
00:03:17.406 --> 00:03:19.032
June was right.

64
00:03:19.658 --> 00:03:21.910
Come on. My car's parked
around the corner.

65
00:03:21.993 --> 00:03:23.704
I'm taking you to your next stop.

66
00:04:01.366 --> 00:04:02.868
Daisy?

67
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:05.078
Talia? It's time for your treatment.

68
00:04:10.876 --> 00:04:13.170
Praise be. Agnes.

69
00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:15.255
Your matches are a success.

70
00:04:19.301 --> 00:04:20.802
Is this it?

71
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:25.307
He has smiled upon you.

72
00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:27.476
These are men chosen by God.

73
00:04:27.559 --> 00:04:29.644
Leaders of Gilead.

74
00:04:29.728 --> 00:04:31.855
This is Commander Weston.

75
00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:36.151
All three men are powerful.
but this is the Commander to impress.

76
00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:40.906
How 'bout a little excitement. hm?

77
00:04:40.989 --> 00:04:43.283
By some miracle. you've done well.

78
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:46.036
And if you keep it up.
you'll live a very comfortable life.

79
00:04:55.670 --> 00:05:00.091
'Member? God has a plan for us all.

80
00:05:11.978 --> 00:05:13.355
Steady now.

81
00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:16.483
Remember. the sting is there
to remind you of your sin.

82
00:05:21.696 --> 00:05:23.573
What was yours?

83
00:05:23.657 --> 00:05:25.951
A name. "Claudia."

84
00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:28.703
Who's Claudia?

85
00:05:28.787 --> 00:05:30.038
My mom.

86
00:05:30.121 --> 00:05:32.415
I haven't spoken to her since I was eight.

87
00:05:32.499 --> 00:05:34.417
I'm not really sure why I got it.

88
00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:36.127
What's yours?

89
00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:40.465
A rose with thorns.

90
00:05:40.549 --> 00:05:42.509
I was drunk.

91
00:05:42.592 --> 00:05:44.177
How basic.

92
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:49.391
Commander Olson has a beachfront
property with over 50 acres.

93
00:05:49.474 --> 00:05:52.143
but Commander Pierce
has a 10 handicap in golf.

94
00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:53.812
Is that good or bad?

95
00:05:53.895 --> 00:05:55.397
My dad says that it's really good.

96
00:05:56.606 --> 00:05:58.567
Agnes. who did you get?

97
00:05:59.359 --> 00:06:02.112
Uh. Commander Pritzger.
Commander Riley.

98
00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:03.864
and Commander Weston.

99
00:06:03.947 --> 00:06:05.323
Praise be!

100
00:06:05.407 --> 00:06:08.118
Paula's probably peeing herself right now.

101
00:06:08.201 --> 00:06:10.662
Weston runs the Eyes. my Martha says.

102
00:06:10.745 --> 00:06:12.038
Well. why isn't he married already?

103
00:06:12.122 --> 00:06:13.915
He was married. His wife died.

104
00:06:13.999 --> 00:06:15.208
That's so sad.

105
00:06:15.292 --> 00:06:16.543
You'll get to go
to all the state functions.

106
00:06:16.626 --> 00:06:18.879
and you'll probably get a million Marthas.

107
00:06:18.962 --> 00:06:20.171
I'll miss Rosa.

108
00:06:20.255 --> 00:06:21.756
Well. if you marry Weston.

109
00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:24.801
Paula will probably give her to you
as a wedding present.

110
00:06:26.845 --> 00:06:29.180
Uh... have you gotten any matches?

111
00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:31.933
- Mm.
- That's awesome!

112
00:06:32.017 --> 00:06:33.768
Praise be His mercy. seriously.

113
00:06:33.852 --> 00:06:35.312
Who?

114
00:06:35.395 --> 00:06:36.730
Commander Maddox.

115
00:06:36.813 --> 00:06:38.064
Oh. yuck. I'm sorry.

116
00:06:38.148 --> 00:06:40.734
He's the one that tried
to get you drunk. right?

117
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:42.777
Tried? He succeeded.

118
00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:45.572
Commander from the Colonies.

119
00:06:48.074 --> 00:06:50.493
And... Commander Chapin.

120
00:06:52.037 --> 00:06:53.580
I've never heard of him.

121
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:57.876
He's not actually a Commander yet.

122
00:06:57.959 --> 00:06:59.294
Who is he?

123
00:06:59.377 --> 00:07:00.462
My Guardian.

124
00:07:02.756 --> 00:07:04.341
Oh. him?

125
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:06.676
No. your parents are not
going to take him seriously.

126
00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:08.762
He's certainly blessed
in a lot of respects.

127
00:07:08.845 --> 00:07:10.096
Praise be.

128
00:07:16.227 --> 00:07:17.437
Becka. pray. slow down.

129
00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.731
I have to use
the bathroom before class.

130
00:07:19.814 --> 00:07:22.442
Please. I'm not mad at you!
We don't choose our matches.

131
00:07:23.234 --> 00:07:25.195
I told you! I never wanted any of this!

132
00:07:25.278 --> 00:07:27.238
Just please don't marry him.

133
00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:30.075
I don't get to choose any of this!

134
00:07:30.158 --> 00:07:31.910
My parents are going
to choose my husband.

135
00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:33.161
Nobody cares what I want!

136
00:07:34.162 --> 00:07:36.873
I don't want to marry anyone!

137
00:07:36.956 --> 00:07:38.667
I want to jump off a cliff!

138
00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:40.669
Don't be so dramatic!

139
00:07:42.003 --> 00:07:43.213
See?

140
00:07:43.296 --> 00:07:44.798
See?!

141
00:07:44.881 --> 00:07:46.549
You don't even care.

142
00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:49.386
I always hoped that you and I
were the same.

143
00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:52.472
but... maybe we're not.

144
00:07:52.555 --> 00:07:55.392
It's like you want to be little forever.

145
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:58.395
I actually want a husband and babies.

146
00:07:58.478 --> 00:08:00.313
but you're the one
that gets him as a match.

147
00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:13.159
That's Commander Weston.

148
00:08:13.243 --> 00:08:14.577
He's your match. right?

149
00:08:17.622 --> 00:08:18.998
Yeah. That's him.

150
00:08:19.791 --> 00:08:23.378
Commander... what can I do for you?

151
00:08:23.461 --> 00:08:25.588
We'd like your permission to enter.

152
00:08:26.256 --> 00:08:28.383
I need to speak with Aunt Lydia.

153
00:08:28.466 --> 00:08:32.220
New intel recovered
from Boston has led us here.

154
00:08:32.303 --> 00:08:34.848
Are you gonna deny us entry?

155
00:08:36.725 --> 00:08:39.602
No. of course not. Commander.

156
00:08:40.353 --> 00:08:41.521
Thank you.

157
00:08:42.564 --> 00:08:43.565
Let's go!

158
00:08:59.748 --> 00:09:02.333
They're investigating
the Mayday attack.

159
00:09:02.417 --> 00:09:04.377
I overheard my father this morning.

160
00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:06.254
Shu is like a spy. honestly.

161
00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:09.674
Do you think they're gonna cancel class?

162
00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:10.925
Probably not.

163
00:09:11.009 --> 00:09:14.387
Unless they have to hang somebody.
because that could take all day.

164
00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:26.483
Hey.

165
00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:28.234
You were asleep for 14 hours.

166
00:09:28.318 --> 00:09:30.195
I was starting to worry about you.

167
00:09:31.279 --> 00:09:32.739
Where's Linda?

168
00:09:32.822 --> 00:09:34.699
Oh. she dropped you off.

169
00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:37.035
This is my place. I'm Rita.

170
00:09:38.369 --> 00:09:39.704
Uh. first things first.

171
00:09:39.788 --> 00:09:43.208
I have a friend in Immigration
who is making a new passport for you

172
00:09:43.291 --> 00:09:44.918
so we can get you out of Canada.

173
00:09:45.001 --> 00:09:46.044
Out where?

174
00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:47.253
Well...

175
00:09:47.337 --> 00:09:50.131
...the UK has retinal scans now.
so that's not an option anymore.

176
00:09:50.215 --> 00:09:54.677
So. I got you on a freight plane
that leaves on Saturday for Colombia.

177
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:56.012
Colombia?

178
00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:58.139
Like. South America?

179
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:00.517
Yes. We have a contact on the ground

180
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:02.685
that will get you re-homed
and put in a school...

181
00:10:02.769 --> 00:10:03.895
I don't even speak Spanish.

182
00:10:03.978 --> 00:10:05.021
Oh. you'll learn.

183
00:10:05.438 --> 00:10:08.525
I don't want to go to Colombia.
I want to go home.

184
00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:10.944
This is so fucking unfair!

185
00:10:11.027 --> 00:10:12.112
Yes. it is.

186
00:10:12.195 --> 00:10:13.822
They're the ones that should have to hide!

187
00:10:13.905 --> 00:10:15.782
- Loaded up like freight on a plane...
- Do you like cats?

188
00:10:16.491 --> 00:10:17.492
What?

189
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:20.453
Some people find it therapeutic
to pet an animal.

190
00:10:24.165 --> 00:10:26.084
They killed my parents.

191
00:10:27.043 --> 00:10:28.253
I know.

192
00:10:30.004 --> 00:10:31.881
Gilead will always be looking for you.

193
00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:35.009
So. as long as you are in Canada.
you're in danger.

194
00:10:37.470 --> 00:10:39.889
No one's ever said that.

195
00:10:39.973 --> 00:10:42.267
like... ever.

196
00:10:54.112 --> 00:10:55.738
- It's good.
- Thank you.

197
00:10:55.822 --> 00:10:57.282
I'm in culinary school.

198
00:10:57.365 --> 00:10:59.450
Nice to have your own life.

199
00:10:59.951 --> 00:11:01.703
Yes. it is.

200
00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:03.663
I didn't for a very long time.

201
00:11:05.999 --> 00:11:09.043
Listen. Melanie and Neil
knew this was a possibility.

202
00:11:09.127 --> 00:11:11.045
They set aside some money for you.

203
00:11:11.129 --> 00:11:13.590
It's not much.
but it was a lot for them.

204
00:11:14.257 --> 00:11:15.967
They should've told me.

205
00:11:21.472 --> 00:11:23.391
Do you know anything
about my real parents?

206
00:11:23.808 --> 00:11:25.685
Just that they got you out of Gilead.

207
00:11:25.768 --> 00:11:27.645
They wanted a better life for you.

208
00:11:27.729 --> 00:11:29.647
You're like their Moses.

209
00:11:29.731 --> 00:11:31.608
Are they still there?

210
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:32.692
No.

211
00:11:32.775 --> 00:11:34.611
They're not alive anymore.

212
00:11:39.991 --> 00:11:41.784
Fuck Gilead.

213
00:11:42.285 --> 00:11:44.162
I'm trying my best.

214
00:11:49.375 --> 00:11:50.668
Thank you for picking it up.

215
00:11:50.752 --> 00:11:51.920
Yeah.

216
00:11:52.003 --> 00:11:55.924
Okay. so let me know when you want me
to pick her up on Saturday.

217
00:11:56.007 --> 00:11:57.717
I'm not gonna run away.

218
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.386
I can't just keep running my whole life.

219
00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:02.347
I wanna join you.

220
00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:03.431
Mayday.

221
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:06.517
You are hurt and confused. And angry.

222
00:12:06.601 --> 00:12:09.062
And anger gives you adrenaline.
Makes you feel brave.

223
00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:10.772
What's wrong with being brave?

224
00:12:11.981 --> 00:12:13.441
I said. "Feel brave."

225
00:12:13.524 --> 00:12:14.525
There's a difference.

226
00:12:14.609 --> 00:12:16.569
I wanna talk to June.

227
00:12:19.489 --> 00:12:21.199
Okay. I'll. uh. I'll call you later.

228
00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:22.617
I'm serious.

229
00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:24.702
I'm not getting on that plane.

230
00:12:24.786 --> 00:12:28.248
They killed my parents.
And I can't let them get away with that.

231
00:12:28.331 --> 00:12:31.918
So. if you guys don't let me join you.
I'll find some other way to fight.

232
00:12:32.961 --> 00:12:34.545
Let me talk to June.

233
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:42.470
Wait. wait. wait.
Uh. we've done it before.

234
00:12:42.553 --> 00:12:44.764
Yeah. but not with a minor.
It's probably illegal.

235
00:12:44.847 --> 00:12:47.058
June has a plan how to do it.

236
00:12:47.141 --> 00:12:49.185
She's just been waiting for a girl
the right age to come along...

237
00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:50.853
Well. of course. June has a plan.

238
00:12:50.937 --> 00:12:53.106
I mean. it's not as if she doesn't
have a horse in the race.

239
00:12:53.189 --> 00:12:56.025
But this kid is emotional.
She's just lost her parents.

240
00:12:57.026 --> 00:12:59.570
Besides. she doesn't
understand what this is.

241
00:13:00.446 --> 00:13:02.115
Yes. I do.

242
00:13:02.198 --> 00:13:05.910
We learned about Mayday in school
when we studied the American War.

243
00:13:05.994 --> 00:13:09.789
Also. stop talking about me
in front of me like I'm not even here.

244
00:13:10.456 --> 00:13:11.958
Let me help.

245
00:13:12.041 --> 00:13:13.668
I've got nothing left to lose.

246
00:13:14.210 --> 00:13:15.211
Sure. you do.

247
00:13:22.093 --> 00:13:23.678
Do you know if you're fruitful?

248
00:13:23.761 --> 00:13:24.929
Fruitful?

249
00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:27.015
Uh. have you gotten your period?

250
00:13:29.225 --> 00:13:31.602
No. But no one does.

251
00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:33.521
I only know one girl who got it.

252
00:13:58.421 --> 00:14:00.048
Talia. Mary.

253
00:14:00.131 --> 00:14:01.799
Daisy. Sara.

254
00:14:01.883 --> 00:14:03.843
Commander Weston
would like to speak to you.

255
00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:14.312
This hurt way more than
I thought it would.

256
00:14:14.395 --> 00:14:15.563
- Yeah?
- Mm.

257
00:14:15.646 --> 00:14:17.982
If you think that's spicy.
wait until you get it removed.

258
00:14:18.066 --> 00:14:19.192
Funny.

259
00:14:19.275 --> 00:14:22.028
Soon as you're in Gilead.
they're gonna laser that thing off.

260
00:14:22.111 --> 00:14:23.946
Then why the hell did you make me get it?

261
00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:27.283
Look. have you ever seen
a panhandler on Queen Street without one?

262
00:14:27.366 --> 00:14:29.952
Some Mayday contact
working for the city

263
00:14:30.036 --> 00:14:33.164
had already got me an ID
with a new last name.

264
00:14:33.247 --> 00:14:37.210
"sin" number.
even a rap sheet for petty theft.

265
00:14:37.293 --> 00:14:39.170
We should've gotten you a daisy.

266
00:14:39.253 --> 00:14:42.673
My name's actually Marguerite.
Daisy's just a nickname.

267
00:14:43.341 --> 00:14:46.552
Well. Gilead doesn't know it.
and so we put it on your passport.

268
00:14:47.178 --> 00:14:49.180
And now it's just your name.

269
00:14:52.433 --> 00:14:54.435
And daisies can grow almost anywhere.

270
00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:59.065
Are you gonna teach me how
to kill someone with just my thumbs?

271
00:14:59.148 --> 00:15:01.567
You know? Learn how to protect myself?

272
00:15:01.651 --> 00:15:02.944
Okay.

273
00:15:03.027 --> 00:15:06.197
You protect yourself
by following their rules.

274
00:15:06.280 --> 00:15:08.449
And don't trust anyone
except your handler.

275
00:15:08.533 --> 00:15:11.953
Because at some point.
you are gonna get lonely.

276
00:15:12.036 --> 00:15:13.371
and it's natural to want a friend.

277
00:15:13.454 --> 00:15:14.914
Who?

278
00:15:14.997 --> 00:15:18.376
I mean. for fuck's sake.
those girls think the Earth is flat

279
00:15:18.459 --> 00:15:20.044
and can't even do multiplication.

280
00:15:20.128 --> 00:15:21.921
Don't ever underestimate them.

281
00:15:22.004 --> 00:15:23.548
Ever!

282
00:15:23.631 --> 00:15:26.759
They have spent their lives being
vigilant in a way that you never have.

283
00:15:26.843 --> 00:15:29.220
So. if you go in there thinking
that you are smarter than them.

284
00:15:29.303 --> 00:15:30.388
you will die.

285
00:15:31.514 --> 00:15:32.849
Do you understand me?!

286
00:15:33.266 --> 00:15:34.350
Okay. Yeah.

287
00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:56.372
You may have a seat.

288
00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:04.297
Daisy? Is that your name?

289
00:16:06.007 --> 00:16:07.550
Yes. sir.

290
00:16:07.633 --> 00:16:10.303
Would you like a glass of water?
There's nothing to be nervous about.

291
00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:12.221
I just need to ask you some questions.

292
00:16:12.305 --> 00:16:15.224
Whenever anyone says.
"There's nothing to be nervous about."

293
00:16:15.308 --> 00:16:16.642
they're lying.

294
00:16:16.726 --> 00:16:19.103
If only I had learned
to kill someone with my thumbs.

295
00:16:19.187 --> 00:16:20.646
You were on the school bus
that was attacked.

296
00:16:20.730 --> 00:16:22.231
That must have been very scary.

297
00:16:22.315 --> 00:16:23.399
Yes.

298
00:16:23.482 --> 00:16:24.734
It was.

299
00:16:24.817 --> 00:16:27.320
Did you notice anything strange that day?

300
00:16:27.403 --> 00:16:28.654
Beforehand?

301
00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.907
Anyone behaving differently?

302
00:16:33.159 --> 00:16:35.036
No. sir.

303
00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:38.497
I heard you were very good in a crisis.

304
00:16:40.041 --> 00:16:41.584
You came here recently. yes?

305
00:16:42.585 --> 00:16:44.545
Tell me about your family

306
00:16:44.629 --> 00:16:46.047
back in Toronto.

307
00:16:49.634 --> 00:16:52.011
Um. I was born in Windsor.

308
00:16:52.637 --> 00:16:54.805
My dad worked for a cell phone company.

309
00:16:54.889 --> 00:16:57.141
and my other dad worked in retail.

310
00:16:57.808 --> 00:16:59.894
Okay. and what school
did you go to?

311
00:16:59.977 --> 00:17:01.437
Abbey Canyon.

312
00:17:01.520 --> 00:17:02.855
But I dropped out in grade six

313
00:17:02.939 --> 00:17:04.857
to hitchhike with my boyfriend to Toronto.

314
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:06.192
Good.

315
00:17:06.943 --> 00:17:08.736
All these dudes are so creepy.

316
00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:10.196
Okay. focus.

317
00:17:10.279 --> 00:17:12.740
They're going to interrogate you.
More than once.

318
00:17:12.823 --> 00:17:15.076
We've already been through all this stuff.

319
00:17:15.159 --> 00:17:16.661
I was a good student. you know.

320
00:17:16.744 --> 00:17:18.287
I'm gonna go to college.

321
00:17:18.371 --> 00:17:20.957
Well. when I'm back. I guess.

322
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:24.293
Being a spy will make
for a killer personal essay.

323
00:17:24.377 --> 00:17:28.130
Just get "spy" out of your head.
You are a sponge.

324
00:17:28.214 --> 00:17:31.801
You are there to gather information
and then pass it on to your handler.

325
00:17:34.262 --> 00:17:37.473
What did Linda mean when she said
June had a horse in the race?

326
00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:39.892
You don't need to know that.

327
00:17:45.481 --> 00:17:47.108
June has a daughter.

328
00:17:47.191 --> 00:17:48.568
In Gilead.

329
00:17:48.651 --> 00:17:50.069
And she's about your age.

330
00:17:52.154 --> 00:17:53.614
That sucks.

331
00:17:53.698 --> 00:17:54.991
Mm-hmm.

332
00:18:05.001 --> 00:18:08.796
Before Gilead. this guy worked in crypto.
and now he's a Commander?

333
00:18:11.215 --> 00:18:14.302
Oh. and he's racked up
a couple of restraining orders

334
00:18:14.385 --> 00:18:15.845
for domestic violence.

335
00:18:15.928 --> 00:18:17.638
Just memorize their faces.

336
00:18:18.222 --> 00:18:20.308
Makes it easier when you
don't know much about them.

337
00:18:24.186 --> 00:18:27.148
Hey. What happened once
you went to Toronto?

338
00:18:29.025 --> 00:18:32.862
My boyfriend and I broke up.
and I bounced around for a bit.

339
00:18:34.071 --> 00:18:37.783
I got in a bit of trouble. and. uh...

340
00:18:37.867 --> 00:18:39.869
I wound up living on the streets.

341
00:18:41.787 --> 00:18:43.414
Very dramatic.

342
00:18:43.497 --> 00:18:45.291
Yes. sir.

343
00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:48.878
The Pearl Girls saved my life.

344
00:18:50.212 --> 00:18:51.631
That's not true.

345
00:18:51.714 --> 00:18:54.592
Breathe. you dumb bitch. breathe.

346
00:18:56.177 --> 00:18:57.762
God saved your life.

347
00:19:04.685 --> 00:19:05.686
Yes.

348
00:19:06.812 --> 00:19:08.147
Praise be His mercy.

349
00:19:10.191 --> 00:19:11.942
Well.

350
00:19:12.026 --> 00:19:14.153
I wish you the best of luck here.

351
00:19:15.571 --> 00:19:16.822
You may go.

352
00:19:16.906 --> 00:19:17.948
Under His eye.

353
00:19:18.032 --> 00:19:19.325
Under His eye.

354
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:49.522
Pray. what's the matter?

355
00:19:53.484 --> 00:19:54.568
Nothing.

356
00:19:56.946 --> 00:19:58.197
I'm fine.

357
00:20:03.077 --> 00:20:05.413
I was just questioned by the Eyes.

358
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:07.373
Okay.

359
00:20:08.082 --> 00:20:09.166
They talked to all of us.

360
00:20:11.168 --> 00:20:12.712
The Pearl Girls. I mean.

361
00:20:12.795 --> 00:20:14.505
They're here to protect us.

362
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:15.840
To protect you.

363
00:20:17.633 --> 00:20:19.885
They're going to find
the people who hurt us.

364
00:20:20.511 --> 00:20:21.887
I know.

365
00:20:21.971 --> 00:20:22.972
But...

366
00:20:25.057 --> 00:20:28.060
They have a way of making you feel
like you've done something wrong.

367
00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:30.146
That's what they do.

368
00:20:33.149 --> 00:20:36.861
I realize. with...
all this marriage stuff.

369
00:20:36.944 --> 00:20:39.905
I've kind of left you
to figure things out on your own.

370
00:20:40.781 --> 00:20:42.950
I'm supposed to be your shepherdess

371
00:20:43.033 --> 00:20:44.827
like Aunt Lydia said.

372
00:20:45.327 --> 00:20:48.539
So. do you want to come to my house today?

373
00:20:48.622 --> 00:20:50.499
After school?

374
00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:55.296
I don't need you to feel sorry for me
just because Aunt Lydia made you.

375
00:20:55.379 --> 00:20:57.506
I don't feel sorry for you.

376
00:20:57.590 --> 00:20:59.258
I admire you.

377
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:01.802
You're really brave.

378
00:21:01.886 --> 00:21:03.387
To come here. on your own.

379
00:21:04.346 --> 00:21:06.432
I mean. if the roles were reversed.

380
00:21:06.515 --> 00:21:08.517
and I was in a terrible situation

381
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:10.186
like you were.

382
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:12.605
would I have the strength
to do what you did?

383
00:21:14.231 --> 00:21:15.775
I don't think I would.

384
00:21:33.334 --> 00:21:35.127
Yeah. have a good one.
You're safe here.

385
00:21:36.754 --> 00:21:38.464
Hi. You want one?

386
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.509
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

387
00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.777
Can I get a bottle of water. please?

388
00:22:02.112 --> 00:22:03.739
Do you know that God loves you?

389
00:22:05.115 --> 00:22:06.826
Fuck off. you creepy bitch.

390
00:22:08.160 --> 00:22:11.247
Rita had warned me not to be too eager.

391
00:22:17.878 --> 00:22:20.130
I've seen you around.

392
00:22:20.214 --> 00:22:22.591
You've been out here for a while.

393
00:22:22.675 --> 00:22:24.718
We're staying at a hotel
around the corner.

394
00:22:24.802 --> 00:22:26.929
You're welcome to come
and take a hot shower.

395
00:22:29.181 --> 00:22:31.350
I can get you something nicer than that.

396
00:22:33.853 --> 00:22:35.563
Do you like spaghetti?

397
00:22:35.646 --> 00:22:38.023
So. what's the catch?

398
00:22:38.107 --> 00:22:41.569
No catch. We're just here to show you
that you are one of God's children.

399
00:22:42.611 --> 00:22:45.447
There's laundry there. too.
You can wash your clothes.

400
00:22:45.531 --> 00:22:48.367
Are you gonna. like.
watch me take a shower?

401
00:22:49.368 --> 00:22:51.745
You religious types
are always kinda kinky.

402
00:22:59.378 --> 00:23:01.213
Have you given any thought to your future?

403
00:23:01.297 --> 00:23:04.174
Room service have
a sundae on the menu.

404
00:23:04.258 --> 00:23:06.302
I'm thinking that'll be
in my near future.

405
00:23:06.385 --> 00:23:09.096
I mean. do you feel like you're
living up to your full potential?

406
00:23:09.221 --> 00:23:12.057
It's not your fault.
Society has discarded you.

407
00:23:12.141 --> 00:23:13.559
It's forced you to fend for yourself.

408
00:23:13.642 --> 00:23:16.896
In Gilead. women are valued
and cherished.

409
00:23:17.605 --> 00:23:19.106
They're respected.

410
00:23:19.189 --> 00:23:20.816
I heard...

411
00:23:20.900 --> 00:23:22.318
...women are kept as sex slaves.

412
00:23:22.401 --> 00:23:24.653
And what about here?
How are women treated?

413
00:23:24.737 --> 00:23:26.488
Think about why you've been told that.

414
00:23:26.572 --> 00:23:29.909
If women here knew that they'd
be treated like gold in Gilead.

415
00:23:29.992 --> 00:23:31.327
they would all want to live there.

416
00:23:33.787 --> 00:23:36.081
Mm. Sweet!

417
00:23:43.547 --> 00:23:46.050
They don't want you
to question the status quo.

418
00:24:01.148 --> 00:24:03.859
Don't you think you deserve better
than what you've received?

419
00:24:03.943 --> 00:24:06.487
Shh! Give me a second.
I want to see what happens.

420
00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:08.155
The bird blows him up with dynamite.

421
00:24:09.406 --> 00:24:10.950
Thought you weren't allowed to watch TV.

422
00:24:11.033 --> 00:24:12.201
I don't miss it.

423
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:13.869
You'd be amazed.

424
00:24:13.953 --> 00:24:16.497
Once you let go of all the things
that waste your time.

425
00:24:16.580 --> 00:24:17.915
how quickly you feel fulfilled.

426
00:24:17.998 --> 00:24:20.542
Well. see ya.

427
00:24:20.626 --> 00:24:21.669
Uh. wait. Hold on.

428
00:24:21.752 --> 00:24:24.254
I knew it. I knew there'd be a catch.

429
00:24:24.338 --> 00:24:26.882
You're welcome to leave
any time you'd like.

430
00:24:26.966 --> 00:24:28.717
We'd just like to say a prayer for you.

431
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:36.100
Lord. our God. please protect
this precious child of Yours.

432
00:24:36.183 --> 00:24:38.560
and let her know that she is loved by You.

433
00:24:39.311 --> 00:24:41.981
Let her understand
that she is worthy of love.

434
00:24:42.064 --> 00:24:43.983
Not just the love of others.

435
00:24:44.066 --> 00:24:45.359
but of herself.

436
00:24:45.442 --> 00:24:47.695
Let her know that she is not alone.

437
00:24:47.778 --> 00:24:49.154
she has never been alone.

438
00:24:49.238 --> 00:24:50.864
and she will never be alone.

439
00:24:53.951 --> 00:24:55.244
You know those pictures

440
00:24:55.327 --> 00:24:58.664
where. at first. you see either
an old hag or a beautiful woman?

441
00:24:59.248 --> 00:25:02.376
Then someone shows you the trick
and you can see the other.

442
00:25:02.459 --> 00:25:04.962
After that. you can flip back and forth.

443
00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:07.047
But now you know they're both there.

444
00:25:07.131 --> 00:25:09.341
You can't unsee the other picture.

445
00:25:09.425 --> 00:25:11.802
No matter how hard you try.

446
00:25:15.097 --> 00:25:17.182
This is a serious dollhouse.

447
00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:19.685
It'll be put in storage soon.

448
00:25:19.768 --> 00:25:21.020
Once I'm engaged.

449
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:25.149
Saved for my daughter.

450
00:25:25.232 --> 00:25:26.233
God willing.

451
00:25:28.569 --> 00:25:32.531
This dress is for my Home Visits.
With my matches.

452
00:25:33.198 --> 00:25:36.326
I don't know anyone in real life
who has a bedroom like this.

453
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:39.038
It's like someone's Mood Board.

454
00:25:39.830 --> 00:25:41.582
Is that a good thing?

455
00:25:41.665 --> 00:25:44.710
It's the bedroom of every
little girl's dreams. basically.

456
00:25:45.461 --> 00:25:47.963
I've never seen the Pearl Girl dormitory.

457
00:25:48.047 --> 00:25:49.423
Why would you?

458
00:25:52.009 --> 00:25:53.427
The Eyes searched it.

459
00:25:54.470 --> 00:25:55.637
The dormitory.

460
00:25:57.264 --> 00:25:59.475
They searched my house once.

461
00:25:59.558 --> 00:26:01.560
When I was younger. in Colorado.

462
00:26:02.269 --> 00:26:03.645
They even took things.

463
00:26:03.729 --> 00:26:06.023
But nothing came of it.

464
00:26:09.568 --> 00:26:10.652
What was your bedroom like?

465
00:26:11.570 --> 00:26:12.654
From before?

466
00:26:12.738 --> 00:26:15.866
Um. normal. I guess.

467
00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:19.328
A bed. a desk.

468
00:26:19.411 --> 00:26:21.622
posters on the wall
of my favorite bands.

469
00:26:21.705 --> 00:26:23.040
Like who?

470
00:26:23.123 --> 00:26:25.292
The Replacements. The Sundays.

471
00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:28.754
I guess I wouldn't know any of them.

472
00:26:29.213 --> 00:26:32.549
I'm not gonna sing it for you if that's
what you're trying to get me to do.

473
00:26:32.674 --> 00:26:34.760
You know.

474
00:26:34.843 --> 00:26:37.846
The usual shoe-gazing. emo stuff.

475
00:26:38.722 --> 00:26:40.641
Songs about falling in love.

476
00:26:40.724 --> 00:26:43.018
breaking up. being dumped.

477
00:26:43.102 --> 00:26:44.144
feeling sad about it.

478
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:46.897
Or. like...

479
00:26:46.980 --> 00:26:49.608
...anthems about being single
and a badass.

480
00:26:50.943 --> 00:26:52.778
I like working out to those ones.

481
00:26:55.114 --> 00:26:56.323
Or. I did.

482
00:27:00.744 --> 00:27:02.037
What?

483
00:27:02.121 --> 00:27:03.413
It sounds horrible.

484
00:27:04.873 --> 00:27:06.667
Well. you haven't heard it yet.

485
00:27:06.750 --> 00:27:08.752
Not the music. Living that way.

486
00:27:09.962 --> 00:27:14.842
I mean. I guess it sounds
kinda bad the way I said it.

487
00:27:15.384 --> 00:27:18.887
And sure. dating or whatever can be hard.

488
00:27:18.971 --> 00:27:21.431
but it can also be amazing

489
00:27:21.515 --> 00:27:23.392
when you find the right person.

490
00:27:23.475 --> 00:27:25.018
At least we got to choose.

491
00:27:26.895 --> 00:27:27.980
We don't need that here.

492
00:27:28.063 --> 00:27:30.899
It's a lot less confusing.

493
00:27:30.983 --> 00:27:33.986
It's because your worth
has already been decided for you.

494
00:27:34.820 --> 00:27:36.864
You don't even need a personality.

495
00:27:39.283 --> 00:27:40.701
Pray. I'm sorry.

496
00:27:41.201 --> 00:27:44.580
Obviously. there is much wisdom
to how it is done here.

497
00:27:46.582 --> 00:27:50.711
It's just... very foreign to me.

498
00:27:55.549 --> 00:27:57.968
These are things I found in the garden.

499
00:27:58.051 --> 00:27:59.511
Or at the beach.

500
00:28:07.436 --> 00:28:10.272
I made up stories about
who owned them before.

501
00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:13.859
You probably know what they all are.

502
00:28:16.028 --> 00:28:19.531
But like. I thought this was given
as a token of love.

503
00:28:19.615 --> 00:28:21.158
Oh. man.

504
00:28:22.117 --> 00:28:24.745
Shady gas stations used
to have these for addicts.

505
00:28:24.828 --> 00:28:26.204
They just put the flower in them.

506
00:28:26.288 --> 00:28:28.206
so they don't get in trouble
for selling crack pipes.

507
00:28:28.290 --> 00:28:30.000
I don't understand.

508
00:28:30.083 --> 00:28:31.084
Explain.

509
00:28:31.168 --> 00:28:33.378
Where do I even begin?

510
00:28:34.463 --> 00:28:36.632
I realized I was an asshole.

511
00:28:36.715 --> 00:28:39.676
Why destroy her fantasy
with an ugly reality?

512
00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:41.637
Life was about to do that for her.

513
00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:43.055
And without my help.

514
00:28:43.138 --> 00:28:46.433
Yeah... I mean. you're close.

515
00:28:46.516 --> 00:28:49.186
This is for Valentine's Day.

516
00:28:52.105 --> 00:28:53.190
You're lying.

517
00:28:55.150 --> 00:28:56.652
You don't trust me.

518
00:28:58.195 --> 00:29:01.073
No. I just like your version better.

519
00:29:01.990 --> 00:29:05.035
There are some messed-up
things where I'm from.

520
00:29:05.118 --> 00:29:06.203
and...

521
00:29:06.286 --> 00:29:09.706
And I guess I just sort of
became used to seeing them.

522
00:29:11.750 --> 00:29:14.419
I got used to seeing people in pain.

523
00:29:14.503 --> 00:29:15.671
suffering.

524
00:29:16.546 --> 00:29:18.256
And I shouldn't have.

525
00:29:22.761 --> 00:29:24.763
I guess maybe I should try that on.

526
00:29:43.991 --> 00:29:45.033
Please.

527
00:29:59.339 --> 00:30:01.091
We're honored to have you here.

528
00:30:01.675 --> 00:30:04.845
We've always felt our Hulda
to be a special young woman.

529
00:30:06.388 --> 00:30:11.435
...pious. meek. obedient.
A product of Gilead's teachings.

530
00:30:11.518 --> 00:30:13.937
A daughter who.
in the benevolence of God's grace...

531
00:30:14.021 --> 00:30:16.940
...has grown into the kind of young woman
Mrs. MacKenzie and I

532
00:30:17.024 --> 00:30:18.525
had always hoped she'd be.

533
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:23.488
I'm so glad to hear that.
All important qualities.

534
00:30:24.364 --> 00:30:26.575
And pleasing to the eye as well.

535
00:30:29.327 --> 00:30:30.704
Praise be His gifts.

536
00:30:38.170 --> 00:30:40.714
Clearly a very well-bred girl.

537
00:30:40.797 --> 00:30:42.299
A credit to the two of you.

538
00:30:42.382 --> 00:30:45.552
And perhaps even more impressive
that she was able to become

539
00:30:45.635 --> 00:30:49.097
such a Godly girl.
in spite of her conception.

540
00:30:51.433 --> 00:30:52.768
Praise be.

541
00:30:57.773 --> 00:31:00.275
Thank you for honoring us with your visit.

542
00:31:08.658 --> 00:31:12.204
I don't care if he's in charge
of economic growth. He's insufferable.

543
00:31:12.287 --> 00:31:15.040
Well. by God's grace. we have
other suitors paying us a visit.

544
00:31:17.459 --> 00:31:20.295
Welcome to our home.

545
00:31:20.378 --> 00:31:22.506
Is it Commander Chapin?

546
00:31:22.589 --> 00:31:25.217
Not yet. sir. Um. not officially.

547
00:31:25.300 --> 00:31:26.301
In a few weeks.

548
00:31:26.384 --> 00:31:28.261
You live in
the Guardian barracks. correct?

549
00:31:28.345 --> 00:31:29.805
Yes. sir.

550
00:31:29.888 --> 00:31:32.474
So. where do you plan
to settle after marriage?

551
00:31:32.557 --> 00:31:35.102
Well. the. uh. Gilead Army
has approved a house.

552
00:31:35.185 --> 00:31:37.604
Unfortunately.
it would not be to the level

553
00:31:37.687 --> 00:31:39.189
which your daughter has become accustomed.

554
00:31:39.272 --> 00:31:40.440
But it... it would be nearby.

555
00:31:40.524 --> 00:31:43.485
You know. I... I thought you might like
to be close to your family.

556
00:31:43.985 --> 00:31:45.195
And your friends.

557
00:31:45.278 --> 00:31:46.530
That's considerate.

558
00:31:46.613 --> 00:31:49.116
Becka's our only child.
She's our gift from God.

559
00:31:49.199 --> 00:31:53.245
Although I cannot offer much
in the way of material comfort yet.

560
00:31:53.328 --> 00:31:56.039
I promise I'll do everything I can

561
00:31:56.123 --> 00:31:58.750
to ensure your daughter's
continued service to God.

562
00:31:59.459 --> 00:32:00.961
And her happiness.

563
00:32:01.837 --> 00:32:04.214
Can I offer you a scotch. Commander?

564
00:32:04.297 --> 00:32:06.174
With what you've been dealing with.
I can imagine

565
00:32:06.258 --> 00:32:08.426
you might need something
stronger than that tea.

566
00:32:08.510 --> 00:32:10.929
Thank you. Uh. I'll take it neat.

567
00:32:11.012 --> 00:32:15.600
Oh. certainly. Commander MacKenzie. too.
has been consumed with his work.

568
00:32:15.684 --> 00:32:17.185
given all the fighting at the Boston b...

569
00:32:17.269 --> 00:32:19.646
I... I... I don't want to.
uh. talk shop today.

570
00:32:21.857 --> 00:32:25.152
Well. thank you.

571
00:32:25.819 --> 00:32:29.865
I have to say. Agnes...

572
00:32:29.948 --> 00:32:31.074
is very impressive.

573
00:32:32.784 --> 00:32:35.996
Aunt Lydia has produced
Gilead's finest young women

574
00:32:36.079 --> 00:32:38.165
through unyielding discipline.

575
00:32:38.248 --> 00:32:40.917
It's necessary to preserve their innocence

576
00:32:41.001 --> 00:32:43.336
as God intended it to be.

577
00:32:43.420 --> 00:32:44.754
Such a wise mother.

578
00:32:45.922 --> 00:32:47.257
You're very lucky.

579
00:32:49.885 --> 00:32:53.346
I will always be grateful for the love
and care my mother showed me.

580
00:32:56.057 --> 00:32:59.311
Well. Agnes. Is there anything
you'd like to ask me?

581
00:32:59.394 --> 00:33:02.480
Agnes would never. uh.
presume to impinge upon...

582
00:33:02.564 --> 00:33:03.690
No.

583
00:33:06.610 --> 00:33:11.823
I only hope I can measure up
to your expectations of a wife.

584
00:33:13.950 --> 00:33:16.369
Especially given
you've been married before.

585
00:33:22.292 --> 00:33:24.419
Could I offer you some more scotch?

586
00:33:24.502 --> 00:33:27.214
Actually. I think it is time
for me to head out.

587
00:33:27.297 --> 00:33:28.924
Mm. yes.

588
00:33:45.899 --> 00:33:49.361
Thank you so much
for your hospitality. Mrs. MacKenzie.

589
00:33:49.444 --> 00:33:51.863
The honor was ours. Praise be.

590
00:33:52.614 --> 00:33:54.532
My wife died in childbirth.

591
00:33:56.618 --> 00:33:59.663
It was the worst day of my life.
the day I lost my child.

592
00:34:01.748 --> 00:34:02.832
Under His eye.

593
00:34:08.713 --> 00:34:12.634
Get far. far away from me
before I hit you.

594
00:34:14.552 --> 00:34:16.680
- I'm sorry...
- Fuck your sorries.

595
00:34:17.597 --> 00:34:19.683
You stupid. selfish girl.

596
00:35:20.952 --> 00:35:23.580
Hey. you know smoking's
not allowed. right?

597
00:35:23.663 --> 00:35:25.123
I'm sorry. I just...

598
00:35:34.215 --> 00:35:36.134
Do you think I have a personality?

599
00:35:39.846 --> 00:35:40.847
What?

600
00:35:40.930 --> 00:35:43.516
A personality. Do you see me for my...

601
00:35:44.768 --> 00:35:46.478
- Never mind.
- Yes.

602
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:50.315
I do.

603
00:35:57.155 --> 00:35:58.239
I see it.

604
00:36:01.159 --> 00:36:03.578
What difference does it make?
It doesn't matter here.

605
00:36:09.084 --> 00:36:10.710
Did you have a nice visit with Becka?

606
00:36:21.137 --> 00:36:22.847
You should go back inside.

607
00:36:38.238 --> 00:36:41.074
Girls. on your knees.

608
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:45.704
And pray.

609
00:36:45.787 --> 00:36:48.039
Pray for the soul of one of your sisters.

610
00:36:49.416 --> 00:36:51.751
For she has been deceiving us.

611
00:36:53.169 --> 00:36:54.796
But God sees all.

612
00:36:54.879 --> 00:36:56.005
And so too. the Eyes.

613
00:36:57.507 --> 00:36:58.758
They have found her out.

614
00:36:58.842 --> 00:37:00.385
and now she will be punished.

615
00:37:11.730 --> 00:37:14.107
No. no. no! No. no. no! No!

616
00:37:14.190 --> 00:37:15.984
Please! Please!

617
00:37:16.067 --> 00:37:17.485
Please! No! Aunt Vidala!

618
00:37:17.569 --> 00:37:18.570
Aunt Vidala! No!

619
00:37:18.653 --> 00:37:20.321
No! No!

620
00:37:20.405 --> 00:37:22.824
Aunt Vidala! Aunt Vidala!
Please! Please! Please!

621
00:37:22.907 --> 00:37:25.118
Please! No! No!

622
00:37:25.201 --> 00:37:26.828
Please! No! No!

623
00:37:26.911 --> 00:37:28.663
No! No!

624
00:37:34.753 --> 00:37:36.379
God's will is done.

625
00:37:36.921 --> 00:37:38.256
Now off to bed.

626
00:37:58.026 --> 00:38:00.737
I've always found a brisk walk
clears the head.

627
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:03.573
Blessed evening. Mrs. MacKenzie.
I didn't hear you come in.

628
00:38:03.656 --> 00:38:04.866
Where's Agnes?

629
00:38:05.492 --> 00:38:08.995
I'm finally ready to confront her
about her ingratitude.

630
00:38:10.079 --> 00:38:11.623
I believe she's in her room.

631
00:38:11.706 --> 00:38:15.084
I assume you know of her indiscretion
with Commander Weston?

632
00:38:16.503 --> 00:38:19.005
You Marthas always seem
to have time to gossip.

633
00:38:19.631 --> 00:38:21.132
Perhaps...

634
00:38:23.301 --> 00:38:25.929
Commander Weston isn't
the right choice for Agnes.

635
00:38:27.514 --> 00:38:30.266
It's not your place
to have an opinion. is it?

636
00:38:31.518 --> 00:38:34.979
My apologies. Mrs. MacKenzie.

637
00:38:47.784 --> 00:38:50.245
That was quite the little
rebellion you staged.

638
00:38:51.996 --> 00:38:54.123
I suppose you thought that was brave?

639
00:39:00.213 --> 00:39:01.714
I'm sorry. Mother.

640
00:39:05.593 --> 00:39:08.680
When I was a therapist.
I dealt with a lot of girls like you.

641
00:39:09.347 --> 00:39:11.391
All of them just as misguided.

642
00:39:22.318 --> 00:39:25.363
But it seems Commander Weston
likes a challenge.

643
00:39:27.907 --> 00:39:29.200
He still wants you.

644
00:39:30.076 --> 00:39:32.745
Men like that enjoy a stubborn spirit.

645
00:39:33.371 --> 00:39:37.500
It's no fun breaking in a horse
that's already docile.

646
00:39:53.266 --> 00:39:54.434
Lord our God.

647
00:39:54.517 --> 00:39:56.686
please protect
this precious child of Yours

648
00:39:56.769 --> 00:39:58.897
and let her know that she is loved by You.

649
00:39:59.689 --> 00:40:03.151
Lord our God. please protect
this precious child of Yours

650
00:40:03.234 --> 00:40:05.403
and let her know that she is loved by You.

651
00:40:05.862 --> 00:40:09.032
Lord our God. please protect
this precious child of Yours

652
00:40:09.115 --> 00:40:11.701
and let her know that she is
loved by you.

653
00:40:14.746 --> 00:40:16.497
It's weird. the things you miss.

654
00:40:16.581 --> 00:40:19.167
Like billboards with ads for light beer.

655
00:40:19.250 --> 00:40:22.462
personal injury lawyers. and outlet malls.

656
00:40:34.182 --> 00:40:36.309
In Gilead. they paint them black.

657
00:40:36.392 --> 00:40:38.895
Like empty chalkboards.

658
00:41:18.476 --> 00:41:19.894
Here we are.

659
00:41:22.772 --> 00:41:24.232
This is the border?

660
00:41:43.418 --> 00:41:45.670
These gentlemen will take you
the rest of the way.

661
00:41:45.753 --> 00:41:46.879
You're not coming with me?

662
00:41:46.963 --> 00:41:48.715
Don't worry.
They'll take good care of you.

663
00:41:49.966 --> 00:41:51.718
I know it looks sketchy.

664
00:41:51.801 --> 00:41:53.928
but it's to cut through the red tape.

665
00:41:54.012 --> 00:41:55.805
They have a friend in Border Patrol.

666
00:41:59.100 --> 00:42:00.476
Under His eye.

667
00:42:02.437 --> 00:42:04.897
This is Daisy. She's a little nervous.

668
00:42:04.981 --> 00:42:07.567
but we've told her
that she's in good hands.

669
00:42:07.650 --> 00:42:08.985
That's right. Daisy.

670
00:42:10.820 --> 00:42:12.488
Good luck.

671
00:42:16.576 --> 00:42:17.827
We'll be praying for you.

672
00:42:23.624 --> 00:42:25.418
- Hey!
- It's contraband.

673
00:42:26.961 --> 00:42:30.631
I mean... you won't need it.

674
00:42:53.821 --> 00:42:56.407
There comes a time
when you have to take action.

675
00:42:56.491 --> 00:42:58.618
when you have to choose your own destiny.

676
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:01.913
We were teenage girls.

677
00:43:01.996 --> 00:43:03.456
So. fuck it.

678
00:43:03.539 --> 00:43:04.999
That time was now.
